Most supermarkets in Nairobi bake their own bread, which they sell alongside the loaves from other bakers. Supermarkets kept the cost of in-house baked bread at Sh50, forcing bakers to reverse the recent Sh5 increase in the price of their loaves.
Bakers had adjusted their price two weeks ago to sell at Sh55 for a 400 gramme loaf, while supermarkets maintained the cost of in-house baked bread at Sh50, with budget-sensitive consumers opting for the cheaper option.



