Wheat millers want the government to abolish the 10 percent duty on wheat and return it to zero-rated VAT status in order to cushion consumers against the rising cost of international prices. Manufacturers break weights and measures rules as they seek to keep prices constant. Kenya relies mainly on imports of wheat as the country does not produce enough to meet the annual demand. Detectives seek to hold former Nairobi county boss for 30 days. He was appointed as the seventh Unctad secretary-general on September 1, 2013. The academic cum political activist is seeking political asylum in Kenya.